text: Abdoullah Bamoussa (born June 8, 1986) is an Italian born Moroccan steeplechase runner, 8th at the 2016 European Athletics Championships. ==Biography== He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's 3000 metres steeplechase race; his time of 8:42.81 in the heats did not qualify him for the final. ==Personal best== *3000 m steeplechase: 8:22.00 - Rome, 8 June 2017 (Golden Gala) ==Achievements== {| class="wikitable" width=60% style="font- size:90%; text-align:center;" |- !Year !!Competition !!Venue !!Position !!Event!!Measure!!Notes |- | rowspan=2|2016 | align=left|European Championships | align=left| Amsterdam | 8th | 3000 m steeplechase | 8:35.35 | He ran in a better time 8:32.54, his Personal Best in Round one. |- | align=left|Olympic Games | align=left| Rio de Janeiro | | 3000 m steeplechase | 8:42.81 | |- | 2017 | align=left|World Championships | align=left| London | 26th | 3000 m steeplechase | 8:34.86 | |} ==See also== *Italy at the 2017 World Championships in Athletics *Naturalized athletes of Italy ==References== ==External links== * * Athlete profile at FIDAL web site * Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Italian male steeplechase runners Category:Olympic athletes of Italy Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Italy
title: Abdoullah Bamoussa
